    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-09-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-09-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="531"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d531">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">White</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-09-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 21, 1893</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 123.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of Mr. Webb’s
                    No. 134, of the 5th instant, reporting that Mr. Joseph Glowacki has been again
                    granted permission to enter Russia.</p>
                <p>The Department is gratified to learn that the case is thus closed.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
